snippet.textDisplay:
it shouldn't really surprise me that the bad democracy practices is being used to "fix" youtube.


"In my situation I don't earn enough money. I therefore want to make a group of people with same problem and we will fight to get more money."


"I love animals. I want to fight for animals with a group of people who want the same."


"we need to stand together (whatever that means) and I with people who believe the same are fighting for it"


etc. etc. etc. etc.


Now we all have to vote for the one thing we want the most and f everything/everyone else. that is how democracy works.
This way of thinking is so heavily flawed and the reason why I never vote. Because it has no meaning because the system is flawed.


Now while Matt's "fix" might work in theory. He forgets the fact that there are tons of youtubers who will stop at nothing to misuse his system to f up people and we will be back where we started. Just some few key things has been switched.


If I were to "fix" youtube. I first want to fix root to all the problems: the mindset of pretty much all people. We need everyone who create videos on youtube to be respectful, think of others first and we need much less money running around the platform. Because with money comes greed and with greed comes all the problems we got now.


Some of you might already think. "but that would be impossible" and you are right. It is pretty much impossible. We need a total reboot of how society works and how people reacts towards each other for it to work. But it aren't totally impossible. A group of people could try to take the first step and we need as many people as possible to see that step and believe in it. And who knows. Maybe after 10-20+ years people around the words has changed for the better and we can have good things in life without some mental sick sociopath ruining it for everyone. Or just stupid people in general.
